newsitem.title: UK: NWE naphtha ends flat in quiet trade.
newsitem.headline: NWE naphtha ends flat in quiet trade.

text.p: NWE naphtha was flat to slightly weaker on Friday in a dull pre-weekend market, traders said.
Swaps were assessed around the $192/$193 level for June, with July put $1.0 above there.
Traders said there was little activity on the physical front. The last deal heard was a 15-20,000 pipeline spec cargo which traded late on Thursday at $192.50 cif NWE.
Light Virgin Naphtha cargo prices were pegged around high quotes +$2.75-$3.0, in line with a cargo done out of Immingham on Thursday.
There was talk that a northwest European trader was stockpiling cargoes. Traders said it was not immediately clear whether the player intended to squeeze or pressure the market lower.
